radiographic_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis. Gallbladder is distended, with wall thickening, pericholecystic fluid, and surrounding fat stranding. Multiple gallstones are identified. No evidence of focal lesions in the liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, or adrenal glands. No significant free fluid in the pelvis. Several prominent retroperitoneal lymph nodes. No worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
